```
import { preferences } from '@kit.ArkData';
const pref = await preferences.getPreferences(context, 'storeName');
await pref.put('key', value);
await pref.flush();
const val = await pref.get('key', defaultValue);
```

The service needs a UIAbility context. I'll pass context via an init method. Since controllers/pages have getContext(this), I'll have StorageService.init(context) called from EntryAbility or lazily. Let me make it accept context.

Actually preferences API can be called without context? No — getPreferences requires a Context. I'll provide an init(context) method and store it statically. EntryAbility.onWindowStageCreate can call StorageService.init(this.context).

Let me write it with JSON serialization helpers. Note: preferences put/get with string values. I'll store JSON strings.

